{"post_stream":{"posts":[{"id":37000,"name":"Kyle","username":"ksmit799","avatar_template":"/user_avatar/discourse.urho3d.io/ksmit799/{size}/2848_2.png","created_at":"2020-03-28T15:00:24.687Z","cooked":"\u003cp\u003eHey everyone,\u003c/p\u003e\n\u003cp\u003eI‚Äôve looked through a couple of old threads and I‚Äôm not entirely sure if the advice in them still stands. I‚Äôm wondering if there‚Äôs a hassle-free way to scale the UI to whatever the window size is in a dynamic way (e.g. someone resizes the resizable window, or goes full-screen). Am I missing a simple setting that I need to enable or is it more complex then that? I know that Unity has the canvas scaler component which uses a reference resolution to automatically scale, but I‚Äôve messed around with ui.SetScale and I wasn‚Äôt able to find much success.\u003c/p\u003e\n\u003cp\u003eAny help would be greatly appreciated!\u003c/p\u003e","post_number":1,"post_type":1,"updated_at":"2020-03-28T15:07:38.008Z","reply_count":0,"reply_to_post_number":null,"quote_count":0,"incoming_link_count":18,"reads":27,"readers_count":26,"score":95.4,"yours":false,"topic_id":6024,"topic_slug":"best-way-to-automatically-scale-ui-to-window-size","display_username":"Kyle","primary_group_name":null,"flair_name":null,"flair_url":null,"flair_bg_color":null,"flair_color":null,"version":2,"can_edit":false,"can_delete":false,"can_recover":false,"can_wiki":false,"read":true,"user_title":null,"bookmarked":false,"actions_summary":[],"moderator":false,"admin":false,"staff":false,"user_id":1316,"hidden":false,"trust_level":1,"deleted_at":null,"user_deleted":false,"edit_reason":null,"can_view_edit_history":true,"wiki":false,"can_accept_answer":false,"can_unaccept_answer":false,"accepted_answer":false},{"id":37001,"name":"È≠îÂ§ßÂÜú ùûçùûéùù≥ ÁèæÊãõËúç","username":"Modanung","avatar_template":"/user_avatar/discourse.urho3d.io/modanung/{size}/3290_2.png","created_at":"2020-03-28T15:07:57.759Z","cooked":"\u003cp\u003eSeems like a duplicate of:\u003c/p\u003e\u003caside class=\"quote quote-modified\" data-post=\"1\" data-topic=\"6019\"\u003e\n  \u003cdiv class=\"title\"\u003e\n    \u003cdiv class=\"quote-controls\"\u003e\u003c/div\u003e\n    \u003cimg loading=\"lazy\" alt=\"\" width=\"20\" height=\"20\" src=\"https://avatars.discourse-cdn.com/v4/letter/l/57b2e6/40.png\" class=\"avatar\"\u003e\n    \u003ca href=\"https://discourse.urho3d.io/t/xml-ui-element-relative-sizing/6019\"\u003eXML UI element relative sizing\u003c/a\u003e \u003ca class=\"badge-wrapper  bullet\" href=\"/c/discussions/support/10\"\u003e\u003cspan class=\"badge-category-parent-bg\" style=\"background-color: #25AAE2;\"\u003e\u003c/span\u003e\u003cspan class=\"badge-category-bg\" style=\"background-color: #92278F;\"\u003e\u003c/span\u003e\u003cspan style=\"\" data-drop-close=\"true\" class=\"badge-category clear-badge\" title=\"Someone can help you.\"\u003eSupport\u003c/span\u003e\u003c/a\u003e\n  \u003c/div\u003e\n  \u003cblockquote\u003e\n    Hello, \nI was wondering if there is a way to give UI elements a size relative to the window/parent. I see that it is possible to set a relative position with the ‚ÄúMin Anchor‚Äù/‚ÄúMax Anchor‚Äù/‚ÄúPivot‚Äù attributes but for size attributes only absolute pixels seem to work. Of course I could calculate and adjust the size in code after reading the layout, but if in any way possible I would prefer to have it all in the XML layout file. \n(And another unrelated question, not sure if it warrants another topic‚Ä¶\n  \u003c/blockquote\u003e\n\u003c/aside\u003e\n","post_number":2,"post_type":1,"updated_at":"2020-03-28T15:08:05.839Z","reply_count":1,"reply_to_post_number":null,"quote_count":0,"incoming_link_count":2,"reads":27,"readers_count":26,"score":35.4,"yours":false,"topic_id":6024,"topic_slug":"best-way-to-automatically-scale-ui-to-window-size","display_username":"È≠îÂ§ßÂÜú ùûçùûéùù≥ ÁèæÊãõËúç","primary_group_name":null,"flair_name":null,"flair_url":null,"flair_bg_color":null,"flair_color":null,"version":1,"can_edit":false,"can_delete":false,"can_recover":false,"can_wiki":false,"link_counts":[{"url":"https://discourse.urho3d.io/t/xml-ui-element-relative-sizing/6019","internal":true,"reflection":false,"title":"XML UI element relative sizing","clicks":0}],"read":true,"user_title":"","bookmarked":false,"actions_summary":[{"id":2,"count":1}],"moderator":false,"admin":false,"staff":false,"user_id":192,"hidden":false,"trust_level":0,"deleted_at":null,"user_deleted":false,"edit_reason":null,"can_view_edit_history":true,"wiki":false,"user_suspended":true,"can_accept_answer":false,"can_unaccept_answer":false,"accepted_answer":false},{"id":37060,"name":"Kyle","username":"ksmit799","avatar_template":"/user_avatar/discourse.urho3d.io/ksmit799/{size}/2848_2.png","created_at":"2020-04-01T11:30:41.822Z","cooked":"\u003cp\u003eThanks for the response, I didn‚Äôt see that post before I created this one sorry. I was able to achieve what I wanted to do with the following Lua code:\u003c/p\u003e\n\u003cpre\u003e\u003ccode\u003efunction ResizeUI()\n  local scale = GetScaleFactor(graphics:GetWidth(),\n                               graphics:GetHeight(),\n                               1920, 1080, 0.5)\n  ui:SetScale(scale)\nend\n\nSubscribeToEvent(\"ScreenMode\", \"ResizeUI\")\n\u003c/code\u003e\u003c/pre\u003e\n\u003cp\u003eWhere the GetScaleFactor function is the following (mimicks unity‚Äôs method of scaling):\u003c/p\u003e\n\u003cpre\u003e\u003ccode\u003elocal function GetScaleFactor(width, height, refWidth, refHeight, scaleFactor)\n  return math.pow(width / refWidth, 1.0 - scaleFactor) *\n         math.pow(height / refHeight, scaleFactor)\nend\n\u003c/code\u003e\u003c/pre\u003e\n\u003cp\u003eHowever, I‚Äôm running into issues when attempting to scale a BorderImage object to match the screen size. The BorderImage is used as a background, and has the same width/height of the UI (ui.root.[width/height]). Is there any way to make an image ‚Äòstretch‚Äô to always fill the window? I know this behaviour is possible in other engines but I wasn‚Äôt able to find a function to do it here. Attached is the problem I‚Äôm facing, the white area (a BorderImage) should always stretch to fill the screen. Any help would be greatly appreciated.\u003cbr\u003e\n\u003cdiv class=\"lightbox-wrapper\"\u003e\u003ca class=\"lightbox\" href=\"https://global.discourse-cdn.com/standard17/uploads/urho3d/original/2X/1/1a6fee2472d49bda7c083c4c0e0dab7652e63332.png\" data-download-href=\"/uploads/short-url/3LSdRNtp4fsisQVVuhAM0vO6ZxM.png?dl=1\" title=\"UrhoScaleIssue\" rel=\"nofollow noopener\"\u003e\u003cimg src=\"https://global.discourse-cdn.com/standard17/uploads/urho3d/optimized/2X/1/1a6fee2472d49bda7c083c4c0e0dab7652e63332_2_341x500.png\" alt=\"UrhoScaleIssue\" data-base62-sha1=\"3LSdRNtp4fsisQVVuhAM0vO6ZxM\" width=\"341\" height=\"500\" srcset=\"https://global.discourse-cdn.com/standard17/uploads/urho3d/optimized/2X/1/1a6fee2472d49bda7c083c4c0e0dab7652e63332_2_341x500.png, https://global.discourse-cdn.com/standard17/uploads/urho3d/optimized/2X/1/1a6fee2472d49bda7c083c4c0e0dab7652e63332_2_511x750.png 1.5x, https://global.discourse-cdn.com/standard17/uploads/urho3d/original/2X/1/1a6fee2472d49bda7c083c4c0e0dab7652e63332.png 2x\" data-small-upload=\"https://global.discourse-cdn.com/standard17/uploads/urho3d/optimized/2X/1/1a6fee2472d49bda7c083c4c0e0dab7652e63332_2_10x10.png\"\u003e\u003cdiv class=\"meta\"\u003e\n\u003csvg class=\"fa d-icon d-icon-far-image svg-icon\" aria-hidden=\"true\"\u003e\u003cuse xlink:href=\"#far-image\"\u003e\u003c/use\u003e\u003c/svg\u003e\u003cspan class=\"filename\"\u003eUrhoScaleIssue\u003c/span\u003e\u003cspan class=\"informations\"\u003e651√ó953 20.1 KB\u003c/span\u003e\u003csvg class=\"fa d-icon d-icon-discourse-expand svg-icon\" aria-hidden=\"true\"\u003e\u003cuse xlink:href=\"#discourse-expand\"\u003e\u003c/use\u003e\u003c/svg\u003e\n\u003c/div\u003e\u003c/a\u003e\u003c/div\u003e\u003c/p\u003e","post_number":3,"post_type":1,"updated_a